1. Check if the stack is empty when encountering a division operator. If it is, throw an "invalid_operation" exception.
2. Perform the division operation when encountering a division operator.
3. Perform the other arithmetic operations (addition and multiplication) when encountering the corresponding characters.
4. Pop the top element from the stack after each operation.

The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the input string, as we perform n operations (one for each character in the string). The space complexity is O(1), as we only use a single stack data structure. The energy implications are low, as the algorithm only involves simple arithmetic operations and does not require any complex calculations or data structures.

